Files for HIT (Hyperlinked Invoice Template) invoice mode:

1. Stored Procedure to be loaded to BRM database:
	a. /apps/pin_inv_doc_gen/invoice_bursting_HIT.plb

2. Data Model to be loaded to the BIP server

	a. <repository>/Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/0.0.0.1.xdm

3. HIT .rtf templates to be loaded to BIP server

	a. <repository>/Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo/BRM_Corporate_Correction_Invoice_HIT.rtf
	b. <repository>/Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo/BRM_Corporate_Invoice_HIT.rtf
	c. <repository>/Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo/BRM_Corporate_Replacement_Invoice_HIT.rtf

4. Edit <repository>/Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo/xdo.cfg to add the hyperlink path prefix

Detailed Steps :

1. Backup all your files and Configuration

2. Load the HIT stored procedure
	1. go to BRM machine - $PIN_HOME/apps/pin_inv_doc_gen
	2. sql <credentials>
	3. at the sql prompt do - @invoice_bursting_HIT.plb;
	4. commit;
	5. quit;

3. Set the HIT data model
	1. In the BIP server go to the repository directory
	2. cd to Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/0.0.0.1.xdm
	3. copy _datamod.xdm to _datamodel.xdm.ORIG
	4. copy _datamodel_HIT.xdm _datamodel.xdm
	5. either edit this file OR go to BIP server and edit on the GUI to set parameters like your data source, FTP server, FTP directory etc.

4. Set the HIT .rtf templates
	1. In the BIP server go to the repository directory
	2. cd to Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo	
	3. copy BRM_Corporate_Correction_Invoice.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Correction_Invoice.rtf.ORIG
	4. copy BRM_Corporate_Invoice.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Invoice.rtf.ORIG
	5. copy BRM_Corporate_Replacement_Invoice.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Replacement_Invoice.rtf.ORIG
	
	6. copy BRM_Corporate_Correction_Invoice_HIT.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Correction_Invoice.rtf
	7. copy BRM_Corporate_Invoice_HIT.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Invoice.rtf
	8. copy BRM_Corporate_Replacement_Invoice_HIT.rtf  to BRM_Corporate_Replacement_Invoice.rtf
	(alternately you can load these HIT .rtf template from the catalog page of the BIP server)

	
5. Edit xdo.cfg file
	1. In the BIP server go to the repository directory
	2. cd to Reports/BRM_Invoices/0.0.0.1/BRM_Bursting_Invoice_Report.xdo	
	3. Edit the file xdo.cfg and replace __FTP_REMOTE_DIRECTORY__ with your FTP destination directory 
	

6. Restart BIP server


Notes: HIT mode will use FTP delivery to create the pdf files. 
	We have to do this because the hyperlinks have to point to 
	local files and not links inside BIP server which will not be portable.

	Also Viewing the PDFs should be done from the ftp directory and 
	NOT from the BIP server.  Viewing from the BIP server can be done 
	for individual invoices but cannot click on the hyperlink links 
	for the subord invoices. You have to go to the job of the subords 
	and view the invoices. 

	If you are packaging the pdfs and viewing in another machine you
	might have to copy these files in the same directory structure
	as the source. Or alternatively you can edit the xdo.cfg to give
	the final directory path that will be used in the end.

	For HIT to produce the split pdfs and hyperlinks you need have the
	thresholds set in the /config/business_param and  run
 	normal invoicing with -hierarchy flag 
		- pin_inv_accts -verbose -hierarchy
		- pin_inv_accts -verbose -pay_type 10001
	trial invoicing with the -paytype parameter
		- pin_trial_bill_accts -start xxx -end yyy -pay_type 10007
		- pin_trial_bill_accts -start xxx -end yyy -pay_type 10001

